p2
VA cultural tribute
p3
sVnews
p4
VA cultural programme was conducted by Vijayawada Music Academy at Sri Sivaramakrishna Kshetram. The programme held in memory of Tadepalli Sunderarajyam was inaugurated by Ghantasala Manikyala Rao, a patron of arts and founder president of Sri Vasavi Vignana Peetham.The first item in the cultural fete was a scintillating Bharatanatyam performance by K.V. Devi Nirmala. Though she performed only one item, she impressed with a sparkling thillana in Revata. Devi Nirmala exhibited precise laya gnanam and her foot work was impeccable.Next followed a classical vocal concert by T. Umashanker of Hyderabad, also a vocalist in demand. Umashanker, sporting a deep vibrant voice and good manodharmam, rendered Todi varnam,Vatapi Ganapathim(Hamsadhvani) with some good kalpana swaras,Sarasijanabha sodariin Nagagandhari andSitapathein Khamas. For the main item Umashanker took upBirana Varalichiof Syamasastri in Kalyani. The raga was rendered in a traditional way. He was well supported on the violin by O. Rajasekhar and S. Nageswara Rao on mridangam. Umashanker ended his concert with a Purandaradas keertana.This concert was followed by devotional songs rendered by Umashanker&#8217;s wife, T. Subbalakshmi who is also a fine violinist. Both Umashanker and Subbalakshmi had their musical training in Government Music College, Vijayawada.Some highlights of Subbalakshmi&#8217;s concert wereSri Maha Ganapathi,Sritakamalasritaan Ashtapadi of Jayadeva in Charukesi,Alamelumanga, an Annamacharya Keertana in Kalyani andJayalakshmi Varalakshmi(also an Annamayya keertana) in Lalita. Fine support came from O. Rajasekhar on violin and J. Dattatreya on flute and S. Nageswara Rao on mridangam. The programme was organised by T.V. Subramanyam, vice president and S. Subramanyam, founder secretary of Vijayawada Music Academy.
